NAME
     ruler - find projected distance between two points

SYNOPSIS
     ruler

DESCRIPTION
     ruler is used to find the  projected  distance  between  two
     points  in the active plot.  If the currently plotted box is
     not the currently active box, or if the internal  state  has
     been altered since the last plot an error is generated.

     Once the command is executed a pointer will  appear  on  the
     view  surface.     Click the left mouse button on one point,
     then click it again on a second point.  The  projected  dis-
     tance will be printed.


